# Session 25 Handover — Fumage

## What was done this session

### 1. Fragrance bottle image pipeline — full implementation

Added end-to-end support for displaying official bottle images on fragrance detail pages. The pipeline scrapes Fragrantica for og:image bottle shots, uploads them to Supabase Storage, and stores the public URL in the database.

**Files changed:**

- `prisma/schema.prisma` — added `imageUrl String?` to `Fragrance` model
- `prisma/migrations/20260501000000_add_fragrance_image_url/migration.sql` — `ALTER TABLE "Fragrance" ADD COLUMN "imageUrl" TEXT;` — **pending apply** (DB was unreachable this session; Supabase project appears paused)
- `next.config.js` — added `hnsnmjwdpewgivphxkcn.supabase.co` to `images.remotePatterns` for Next.js `<Image>` component
- `scripts/fetch-fragrance-images.ts` — one-time scraping script; see usage below
- `src/app/fragrances/[slug]/page.tsx` — bottle image renders at top of sidebar when `imageUrl` is set (Next.js `<Image>`, 192×256px, `object-contain`)
- `package.json` / `package-lock.json` — added `cheerio` dev dependency (HTML parser used by the script)

**Script usage (run after DB is reachable):**

```bash
# Test on one fragrance first
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=<service_role_key> \
  npx ts-node --compiler-options '{"module":"CommonJS"}' \
  scripts/fetch-fragrance-images.ts --limit 1 --slug dior-sauvage

# Full run — all 687 fragrances without imageUrl, in popularity order
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=<service_role_key> \
  npx ts-node --compiler-options '{"module":"CommonJS"}' \
  scripts/fetch-fragrance-images.ts
```

`SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` is in Supabase dashboard → Project Settings → API → Service role secret.

The script: searches Fragrantica by name+house, follows the first result, extracts `og:image`, downloads the bottle shot, uploads to Supabase Storage bucket `fragrance-images` (auto-created if absent), updates `fragrance.imageUrl`. 2.5s delay between requests; supports `--dry-run`, `--limit N`, `--slug S`. Failures logged to `image-fetch-failures.log`.

**Commit:** `c701e0b`

